{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/composablearchitecture\/migratingto1.15"]}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.15","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The library has been completely updated for Swift 6 language mode, and now compiles in strict"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"concurrency with no warnings or errors."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The library is now 100% Swift 6 compatible, and has been done in a way that is full backwards"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"compatible. If your project does not have strict concurrency warnings turned on, then updating"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the Composable Architecture to 1.15.0 should not cause any compilation errors. However, if you have"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"strict concurrency turned on, then you may come across a few situations you need to update."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"text":"Enum cases as function references","type":"heading","anchor":"Enum-cases-as-function-references"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is common to use the case of enum as a function, such as mapping on an "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Effect"},{"type":"text","text":" to bundle"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"its output into an action:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["return client.fetch()","  .map(Action.response)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In strict concurrency mode this may fail with a message like this:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineConte